<p>Hello I am new to Haskell and trying to write a function to check if a tree is binary search tree or not . </p>  <p>Below is my code :-</p>  <pre><code> data Tree = Node Int Tree Tree                    | Leaf Int                   deriving (Eq,Show)  val :: Tree -&gt; Int val (Leaf i) = i  isBst :: Tree -&gt; Bool isBst (Leaf i) = True isBst (Node x l r) = if (x &gt;  (val l )) &amp;&amp; (x &lt; (val r)) then True else False </code></pre>  <p>But I get the following error when I execute it . </p>  <pre><code>&lt;interactive&gt;:10:1: Not in scope: ‘isBST’ </code></pre>  <p>Can anyone please help me fix this or help me write a method to <code>determine if a tree is bst or not using haskell</code>.</p>  <p>Can you also please help to <code>make this code exhaustive</code> ?</p>